      <div class="poem-1 col-md-4 col-md-pull-4">
          Dad, we don’t think of you as gone away</br>
          As your journey’s just begun,</br>
          Life holds so many facets</br>
          This earth is only one.</br> </br>
          
          We just think of you as resting</br>
          In a place of warmth and peace</br>
          Where there are no days and years</br>
          And neither sadness and tears.</br> </br>
          
          Dad you were always kind and caring</br>
          And so understanding too</br>
          And if help was ever needed Dad</br>
          It always came from you.</br> </br>
          
          How we wish that you could know today</br>
          How great is our sadness</br>
          That you have passed away.</br> 
      </div>
      
      
      <div class="poem-2 col-md-4 col-md-4">
          We will always think of you as living</br>
          In the hearts of those you touched</br>
          For nothing loved is ever lost</br>
          And you were loved so much.</br> </br>
          
          Your life well lived ls a legacy </br>
          Of joy and pride and pleasure </br>
          A living lasting memory </br>
          Our grateful hearts will treasure </br></br>
          
          So rest in peace dearest Dad</br>
          And thank you for all you’ve done</br>
          As we pray to God to give you</br>
          The crown you’ve truly won.</br>
      </div>
    </div>
    
