      Leslie Nazareth was born  on Aug 19, 1921 to Peter and Ruby Nazareth. Leslie was raised first in Ghatkopar and then in Nazarene 
      Villa, Chembur,  along with his 6 siblings. He completed his studies in Sydenham College, Mumbai. He married his childhood 
      sweetheart, Dr. Olga DaCosta in 1949 and celebrated their Golden wedding anniversary in Chennai in 1999 along with their 3
      children Carol/David Edwin/Susan and Adrian/Zelia
      and two grand children Sarah and Rohit. After a very long career with Shaw Wallace he retired at the young age of 55
      to do social and  charitable work. Leslie was known for his wit and great sense of humour. He had several interests but
      was passionate about golf and bridge. He spent the last last 2.5 years of his life with his youngest child Adrian in Canada 
      where he died peacefully on Dec 26, 2017.
